                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc"/>
                            <title xml:lang="per"/>
                            <note>
                                <p>A copper plate in Persian issued in the name of Aurangzeb
                                    recording a land grant of 525 bīghah of land in the pargana of
                                    Minda (?), suba of Ajmer upon Naẓar ‘Alī Shāh, whose want of
                                    means of subsistence has left him indigent, on the understanding
                                    that he will pray for the perpetuation of his sovereign's
                                    rule.</p>
                                <p>Dated 11 Rabīʻ II regnal year [1]4 (AH 1082, 17 August 1671).</p>
                            </note>
